Client: Commonwealth of technology, Frankfort KY
May,2019- Oct,2019 Role: Sr UI/UX Designer (Salesforces)
Kumar.tangella@ky.gov
Salesforces trailhead : https://trailhead.salesforce.com/en/me/stangella3
Responsibilities:
• As a UX designer, I partnered with designers to work through the early stages of a design or product working from strategy and feature definition into Flow charts, sketching and prototyping, and iterating.
• Adjusted current wireframes to reflect UI/ UX standards.
• Redesigned the interfaces according to established style guide.
• Designing websites/landing page for clients using Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, and Axure RP8
• Adobe Creative Suite Instructor (After Effort).
• Worked on Adobe Experience Manager - Mobile Product. Extended customer on demand portal capabilities and developing scalable backend web services to support various product capabilities
• Created internal portal using wireframe and prototypes.
• Develop detailed storyboards, wireframes, concepts, mockups, and interactive prototypes
• Have delivered Multiple successful live products for Android, iOS and web platforms
• Developed the User Interface with HTML, HTML5, CSS, CSS3, JavaScript, Bootstrap
• Involved in creating, monitoring, and measuring campaigns with Salesforce CRM Marketing.
• Administered Salesforce.com applications and migrated code/data from different environments.
• Customized page layouts for Salesforce.com standard and custom objects.
• Proficient in using VS code based Salesforce.com IDE to develop and deploy force.com software.
• Created multiple Lightning Components, added CSS and Design Parameters that makes the Lightning component look and feel better.
• Lightning web components are custom HTML elements built using HTML and modern JavaScript.
• Created and maintained the data model needed for the custom application. Objects, fields, Record types, page layouts, custom relationship between the objects.
• Created administrative activities like creating queues, custom apps, custom labels, custom settings, custom metadata types, Names credentials and static resources.
• Developed custom Lightning components for customer facing pages and hosted on communities to make them available for customers to access their order summary.
Environment: HTML, CSS3, JavaScript, jQuery, TypeScript, Eclipse, Ajax, DOM, Bit Bucket, Salesforce, wireframes, prototypes, Mockup
